<p><strong><font color="#f0f0f0">New EQ News Site</font> </strong><small>Posted Friday, March 3, 2000 by <a href="mailto:jcsmith@gameznet.com">jcsmith</a></small><br>
I wanted to take the time to plug a new Everquest news site by the name of <a href="http://www.thesky.org">TheSky.Org</a>. How best to describe the site... oh forget it why lie? I'm just too lazy to type it up in my own words. Anyway here's a description from the webmaster.<br><br><blockquote>Just wanted to get the word out that me and a team of friends have started a great new site called TheSky.Org (<a href="http://www.thesky.org">http://www.thesky.org</a>). Our goal: To provide the EverQuest community with an online 'news ticker', updated daily with general news, server specific news, and forum posts by the EQ team. (Our forum logs section will eventually evolve into a megaplex of every post made by any EQ staff member in the past and present!) All info is collected from the many EQ related sites across the internet and presented in clean, "plain jane" form for easy surf-free reading. <br><br>Our hope is that TheSky.Org will not be competition for various sites (like EQLizer), but a gateway of EQ information to all the great sites that are out there.<br><br>So please, drop by and enjoy the fruit of our labors thus far!<br><br>- John "Syruss" Wooldridge (syruss@thesky.org)</blockquote>
</p>
