<a name="newsitem952110285,79219,"></a>
<p><strong><font color="#f0f0f0">Brad On Ruins of Kunark</font> </strong><small>Posted Friday, March 3, 2000 by <a href="mailto:jcsmith@gameznet.com">jcsmith</a></small><br>
<a href="http://www.gamespot.com">Gamespot</a> has posted up an <a href="http://www.gamespot.com/features/kunark_pre/index.html">interview</a> with Everquest producer Brad McQuaid. The interview covers Ruins of Kunark. Here's a highlight...<br><br><blockquote>GameSpot: How [if at all] will Ruins of Kunark specifically address issues like camping static spawns with good loot and specific zone overcrowding? <br><br>McQuaid: It doesn't - it adds a new playable race and a new continent to explore, increasing the size of Norrath by over 30 percent. Improving the camping situation is a continual process of moving treasure around and making sure that highly wanted items are not class specific and the product of quests. Specific zone overcrowding is generally solved by retuning zones, often making less frequented zones</blockquote>
</p>
